  "texts": [
    "Figure 1 shows the architecture of our proposed approach.More specifically, our proposed approach consists of the following steps: (1) Preprocessing text for text normalization and inconsistency removal; (2) Distributional semantic models used to capture text's semantics; (3) The vectors generated by distributional semantic models are combined through our novel vector generation algorithm known as the big-vector generation algorithm to produce dense semantic extensions of the input sentences.",
    "; (4) We then cluster the semantically similar sentences together in a single cluster using the clustering algorithms.",
    "The single cluster is a coherent representation of the most similar sentences.",
    "; (5) Ranking algorithm to obtain scores for each sentence from each cluster; and (6) Normalization of scores for efficient sentence extraction to obtain the summary.",
    "PreprocessingPreprocessing is an essential step in our system."
  ],
